HEADWORD: Morbidity
<hw>Mor*bid"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
quality or state of being morbid.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Morbid quality; disease; sickness.</def> <rj><au>C.
